This repository uses **Project Factory**, a spec-driven multi-agent delivery
framework. Operate under it:

- Read **`AGENTS.md`** for the operating rules and the lifecycle — it is the
  canonical, tool-agnostic entry every agent honors.
- The orchestrator is `skills/project-factory/SKILL.md`; the full playbook is
  `MASTER-PROMPT.md`; the hard gates are `checklists/quality-gates.md`.
- To start: the `project-factory` skill auto-triggers (e.g. "build this to spec",
  "set up project factory"), or run its commands `/project-factory:init` (new
  repo) or `/project-factory:onboard` (existing repo).
- The deterministic loop (`scripts/check-*`, OpenSpec specs, gates, evals,
  trajectory checks, tests) is identical here — it is pure Node + git, not
  Claude-specific. See `docs/portability.md`.
